						<B>TERRORIST ARRESTS</B>
<br>

<br>
It took just 19 pilots to create carnage in America on 9-11 and rewrite the=
 history books for ever. Today, the Saudi Government announced the arrest o=
f 170 Al Qaeda suspects - some of whom, it says, were training to fly to ca=
rry out attacks.=20
<br>

<br>
It's an astonishing figure that evokes a visceral response: How do you imag=
ine a terrorist plot nine times bigger than September 11th? And in the last=
 few hours, it's emerged that the USA has also arrested a leading Al Qaeda =
figure, Hadi al Iraqi - a man wanted in connection with assassination attac=
ks on President Musharraf of Pakistan.  We'll have the latest developments =
on both stories tonight.
<br>

<br>
<B>SUPER RICH</B>
<br>

<br>
If you were a billionaire and really really didn't want to part with your c=
ash to pesky old tax, where would you choose to live?  Belize? Monaco? Caym=
an Islands? Well actually you could do worse than the UK. The IMF has, for =
the very first time,  ranked Britain alongside these tax havens - for the l=
oop hole which allows the super rich who live here to avoid paying up on mo=
ney earned abroad.=20
<br>

<br>
This of course, under the beady watch of a Chancellor whose protestant work=
 ethic and acute awareness of injustice are part of his DNA. Tonight, we'll=
 be asking why there are no plans to close the loophole and whether people =
close to him may actually be profiting from it.
<br>

<br>
<B>ROSTROPOVICH</B>
<br>

<br>
In musical circles, Mstislav Rostropovich, who died today in Moscow, was a =
genius and a world renowned cellist.  In political circles, he was a powerf=
ul emblem of the resistance to Soviet communism.=20
<br>

<br>
The two sides of this extraordinary personality came together most dramatic=
ally on the night the Berlin Wall came down in 1989 - bursting into spontan=
eous concert in support of the pro-democracy protestors that tore down the =
symbol of the Cold War.  Tonight, we speak to a former pupil about his lega=
cy.=20
<br>

<br>
Join me tonight at 10:30pm on BBC2.
<br>

<br>
Emily=20=20=20
<br>
=20
<br>

